Key words:
Polychaeta; 
Paraonidae
; Taxonomy; 
Paradoneis
; new species; Sea of Marmara

Among the great amount of material collected from the Sea of Marmara, 1556 specimens of Paradoneis were found. These specimens belonged to four species, one of which ( P. armata ) was new to the marine fauna of the Sea of Mar- mara and two species ( P. heterochaeta n. sp. , P. longifurcata n. sp. ) were new to science. The fourth species found, P. ilvana , was previously reported from the region (
Çinar et al ., 2011
). These species are described/re-described and discussed in comparison to the closely related congeners.

